{
  "stem": "4345.4",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had a-- I had a good heart, evidently.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was there for two weeks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were a slave labor camp there, and our main job was to take the dead bodies onto tracks, out to the fires.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So can you imagine when they come in, you know, those people when they come to take the bodies and if I would be laying, not moving, they would take me out, too.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So-- and if I was alive, then I had to help take bodies out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I pick myself, you know, up with all my might and I took the two feet from the-- from those dead skeletons, and I would schlep them like this.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the fire was like a little bit further out, there was a fire burning, gasoline fire for the bodies, gasoline fire with bodies.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this was like a constant-- like a torch, constantly burning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then I walked back to the barrack, and I laid down.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But finally, I had hundred-and-six marked fever, so Mitzi Maylor, who was the [GERMAN] in my camp, said-- came over to me with a doctor, a woman doctor from Czechoslovakia, and she said, do me a favor.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Check this child.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She wanted me to go to the kitchen to work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I said, Miss Maylor, I cannot do it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And this doctor came and she said, [SPEAKING GERMAN], two days to live.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I hear this, you know, my mind was OK, and I said, you tell her that she is going to live two days, and I'm going to make it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my friend Sally did work in the kitchen, and she would come to me with food, the bread which had the glass ground in.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People died from that anyway.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
